title: "NeusktchmechArc: A Personal Provenance Transmuting Feeling into Form"
type: generic
authors:
  - family-names: Bhatara
    given-names: Mohit
abstract: >
  NeusktchmechArc is a personal art archive documenting a self-authored
  conceptual framework that explores how lived impressions gradually
  take visual form through symbolic and creative expression. The archive
  incorporates fictional and imaginative elements within its artistic
  narrative, structured around four conceptual phases: Interior Atlas,
  First Emanation, Tranquil Rift, and Integration Phase. It is presented
  as a non-commercial creative work and does not constitute a scientific,
  medical, psychological, legal, or professional methodology.
url: "https://www.neusktchmecharc.site"
